Description:
Expansive Family Home With Huge Triple Garage - On A Landscaped 2 Acres!
Phone Enquiry ID:44440
An expansive family home on a superb, beautifully landscaped 2 acres (8000sqm) right in the heart of Drysdale, perfect for families of any configuration and throughout all stages of life. Just moments from all amenities, yet surrounded by other small acreages with plenty of space in between.
This beautiful, quality-built home is immaculately presented with a long list of features. An exceptional opportunity to acquire an expansive, premium home along with the relaxed, carefree country-meets-surf-coast lifestyle that only the Bellarine Peninsula can offer!
If you’ve given up hope that you’ll ever find a small, centrally located acreage with a ready-made home that can accommodate all the cars, the weekend toys and your tools, as well as enough internal living space to complement, you may have to sit down…. The home and lifestyle you’re looking for actually does exist!
Four large bedrooms, or three plus an office and two bathrooms - impressive Master suite with walk-in robe and ensuite. A beautiful timber kitchen at the heart, surrounded by extra-large formal and informal living and dining zones with north-facing windows allowing abundant natural light to trickle in.
A wide veranda skirts around three sides with beautiful rural outlooks over the gardens to the paddocks behind - and the handyman, car or watersport enthusiast will love the huge 10m x 8m triple rautomatic garage and workshop!
The location is paramount, to say the very least. Just 1km to Drysdale PO, within minutes from an array of quality schooling options, 10 minutes (10km) to Ocean Grove and Point Lonsdale’s surf beaches, 20km to Central Geelong, 15 mins to historic Queenscliff and Queenscliff-Mornington ferry.
Perhaps best of all, Melbourne professionals can say goodbye to their 2-3 hour heavy-traffic commute, and say hello to a relaxed, 12 minute country drive to the Port Phillip Ferry terminal; where they can either enjoy the glorious bay views - instead of tail lights; catch up on the latest news or get a headstart on the day’s workload!
FEATURES:
- Gas ducted heating throughout
- Split system air-conditioning
- Back-to-base security system
- 20,000ltr water tank (and connected to town water)
- Immaculately looked after, quality-built home

Description:
Rural-urban sanctuary on 5 picturesque acres (approx.)
Escape to your own rural sanctuary, but not at the expense of convenience! This picturesque 5 acre (approx.) lifestyle property offers perfect rural-urban fusion, located 3 mins from Drysdale Village and schools, 8 mins from Ocean Grove beaches and 25 mins from Geelong CBD. Set near Basin Reserve and with it's own 'Land for Wildlife' space, this is a rejuvenating escape, and an ideal set-up for equestrian pursuits.
Zoned 'Farming' the undulating land with stands of gumtrees is beautiful, and every room of the home benefits from the peaceful rural vistas. The home is immaculately presented and includes; an entry hall, living room with corner glazing, built-in wood burner and split system AC, large country-style kitchen/meals room with freestanding Chef gas cooker and walk-in pantry, 3 queen-sized bedrooms with floor-to-ceiling built-in robes, bathroom with vanity, separate shower room, laundry and rear access sunroom. This solid home is ideal for extension (STCA).
Outdoor assets include; 4 fenced paddocks and the home acreage, 2 stables and a holding yard, a detached DLUG with adjoining tack room and a large wood/garden shed. The vegetable patch and chicken coop allow a level of organic self-sufficiency.
This peaceful property is the perfect toehold into the 'lifestyle property' market. View ASAP!
- Picturesque 5 acre (approx.) lifestyle property
- An rejuvenating escape set-up for equestrian pursuits
- Immaculately presented 3BR home with lounge, kitchen/meals, 2 wet areas
- Home acreage, 4 paddocks, 2 stables, tack room, DLUG, large wood shed
- Organic self-sufficiency with vegetable patch and chicken coop
- 3 mins to Drysdale Village, 8 mins to Ocean Grove beaches, 25 mins to Geelong CBD

Description:
Brand New Starter or Downsize
There’s nothing quite like the perfection of a brand new home. The smell, the pristine condition and the ability to make it your own. If you’re looking for that perfect downsize or first home, and love the relaxed semi-rural ambiance of Drysdale, why not treat yourself to this inviting, low maintenance home with lots of quality upgrades.
Set in a boutique neighbourhood rich with wetlands, walking trails and a playground, this home is just a short walk from every convenience in the town centre. It’s also within easy reach of the beaches, wineries and restaurants The Bellarine is renowned for.
The design ticks all the boxes. Three bedrooms, master with en suite, kitchen with walk-in pantry, quality appliances, Caesarstone to kitchen and bathrooms and zoned climate control.
Bedrooms and wet areas sit at the front of the plan. The master BR, with walk-through robe and fresh en suite, accesses a protected courtyard. The family bathroom features bath and shower. Stylish Caesarstone is a luxurious treat!
The open plan kitchen/living hub shines with bright triple aspect at the rear, and extends to a spacious entertaining patio. Caesarstone benches blend beautifully with porcelain splash backs, and the Tisira (Ariston) and Omega branded appliances are a boon. Dine indoors or out, but you’ll love the sunshine all year round in this vibrant living zone!
All the attributes you’d expect of a contemporary build are present and guaranteed. These include; Braemar split system with ducted heating and wall-mounted cooling, solar hot water, 2020L tank plumbed to toilets and NBN ready cabling. Handy design features include the laundry with yard access, and garage with internal access.
This picturesque small estate will ensure an exceptional lifestyle, and current demand will ensure an exceptional investment. View without delay!

Description:
Over 1000m2 in the heart of Drysdale
Opportunities like these do not come up often, here lies a renovators or developers dream in a blue-chip location.
It's no secret that our 'little country town' is growing at an exponential rate, and population growth is forecast to continue booming. In case you haven't noticed, there is huge investment being injected into the area via government and private infrastructure (including the $109 million Drysdale Bypass and High St upgrade project). This level of investment is only seen in areas that are a 'sure thing' for future growth, and Drysdale is undoubtedly one of these.
This package includes a quaint and original three-bedroom home with split system air-cons, massive lock-up shed/workshop, and over 1000m2 of land in the heart of Drysdale. Whether your strategy is buy-and-hold, renovate or develop - you are onto a winner here.

Description:
Premium land for an idyllic coastal-rural lifestyle with amazing views
This scenic land offers an idyllic coastal-rural lifestyle in the heart of The Bellarine. Breathtaking views over the undulating hills of The Bellarine and across Port Phillip Bay to the Mornington Peninsula are sure to impress. This rich sweeping aspect will become the focal point of your new contemporary build (STCA). Look forward to the ever changing vista; big watery horizons on clear blue days, storm fronts at the end of a hot spell, and the intoxicating bay and peninsula lights by night.
The land comprises undulating grazing paddocks enhanced by mature shelter-belts and a dam. Ideal for cropping, horticultural and equine pursuits, the rich soil and modest rainfall ensure good productivity and a level of self-sufficiency.
Just 5 minutes to every family convenience in Drysdale, 10 minutes to beautiful bay beaches, 30 mins to Geelong and wonderfully close to highly regarded wineries, eateries and organic producers. This location offers the perfect mix of convenience, privacy and peace.
Choose this sought-after property and enjoy the perfect coastal-rural fusion.
- Approximately 76 acres of scenic land in the heart of The Bellarine
- Breathtaking views over hills and the bay to the Mornington Peninsula
- 5 mins to Drysdale, 10mins to bay beaches, close to wineries, eateries, organic producers
- Magical aspect for a new build (STCA) - watery horizons, storm fronts, night lights
- Undulating paddocks enhanced by mature shelter-belts and a dam
- Ideal for cropping, horticultural and equine pursuits

Description:
Quailty Of Days Gone By!
Set on almost 600m2 is this immaculate 3 bedroom home built to impeccable standards. It has been meticulously maintained over the years and offers buyers 3 separate living zones- formal lounge and dining rooms, kitchen & meals area plus family room with doors that give access to a north facing paved courtyard. A walk in pantry and plenty of cupboard space will please the lady of the house and the extra large double garage with high roller doors make the man of the house smile. All bedroom have built in robes, are generously sized and there is a full ensuite to the master. Central gas heating and a reverse cycle split system air-conditioner keep the home comfortable all year round. Ideally located just minutes to central Drysdale and all amenities. This home is a gem and an inspection will confirm. Be quick to inspect!

Description:
The Land of Opportunity
This is an exclusive and limited opportunity to secure a truly charming home right in the heart of Drysdale with future subdivision potential.
Boasting an array of original features; baltic timber floors, ornate cornices, high ceilings and feature decorative ceiling plaster ensure this property will capture the attention of all those who inspect. Beautiful light and bright finishes are enhanced by an abundance of natural light from various feature windows (complete with original brass fittings).
Generous proportions are a consistent theme throughout; 2 oversized bedroom suites showcase size and scale. A 3rd bedroom offers further flexibility and scope to the floor plan.
The kitchen is a throw-back to yester year when 'practical' ruled; expansive bench space, exceptional storage solutions and a lovely outlook to a good old fashioned backyard. An informal lounge embraces a lovely northerly orientation and is bathed in filtered light.
My personal favourite room is what would have been the formal lounge. Towering high ceilings with orate cornices and dual corner set windows perfectly frame a beautiful garden setting which creates a warm, welcoming and relaxed living zone.
A double (back to back) garage with drive through access to an expansive rear yard ensures this property can cater for not only cars, boat and a caravan. A 'bessa brick' workshop is powered and secure.
As impressive as this property is to the eye, its scope and future subdivision potential is
where it really comes into its own. A land holding of approx. 1012m (20.1m frontage) - General Residential Zone lends itself to various development models (STCA).
An A1 central location ensures this property is perfectly positioned to take full advantage of the local amenities.
This property undoubtedly picks itself as an exceptional prospect in today's property market; a home for today and an exceptional investment for the future.

Description:
Character Home, Back in Time Lifestyle
I have watched this character home evolve and be transformed by the current owners over many years. Now your opportunity is here to purchase and enjoy the restoration and renovation. This period home was originally built in 1938 and moved to the site from Melbourne in 2007 and many hours and days later have resulted in this amazing makeover. Many a relaxing time will be had on the elevated deck while you also enjoy a rural outlook. Step back in time with the established veggie patches on this 1226m2 (approx). A Rocking chair on the front veranda will also step you back in time. What will this lifestyle cost me? Well the home is going to Auction so it is over to you to come and inspect and form your own opinion on the value. Established in the 1840's the historic town of Drysdale still has the feel of a small country town even though development is progressing on its outskirts. We are also very proud to say we have the Heritage Bellarine Railway another historic connection, running steam train rides between Drysdale and Queenscliff. You do not miss out on the day to day amenities here. Everything you need is at your fingertips; schools, medical centres, sporting groups, restaurants, wineries, bike trail and plenty more. Come check out my town and maybe choose that back in time lifestyle.

Description:
Once Upon A Time!
This charming weatherboard cottage oozes character and would be perfectly placed in a fairy tale setting!
Your first impressions will undoubtedly be 'WOW'! You will be greeted by beautifully stunning landscaped gardens and soon after the true wonder of this little weatherboard gem will be revealed. A gorgeous and decorative front porch offers a lovely northerly orientation to capture an abundance of natural light. Upon entry you will be impressed by the towering pressed tin ceilings (3m approx), timber beams and not one but 2 ornate open fireplaces; not to mention various other original features. Stunning timber windows perfectly frame the landscaped gardens and the wide open spaces of the expansive land holding (861m approx).
2 generous bedrooms boast high ceilings and both are bathed in natural light. An equally generous kitchen which looks 'ripe' to be returned to its former glory. An additional sitting/sunroom offers further scope what is already a flexible floor plan.
This fine property looks a wonderful opportunity to secure some genuine blue chip real estate right in the heart Drysdale.
-861m (approx) RESIDENTIAL GROWTH ZONE - SCHEDULE 2

Description:
"PERROWOOD" - 44.58 Ha - 110 Ac (approx.)
This truly magnificent small acreage holding is perfectly suited to the devoted 'horse lover'. The property is superbly equipped for the horse trainer and/or equestrian interests.
'Perrowood' is located on the cusp of the Drysdale township in a highly appreciating area that offers unlimited potential.
The land is also ideal for cattle and sheep, cropping and other farming pursuits. Comprising numerous stables and yards, round yard, tack rooms, site hut, several horse shelters, a magnificent 1,600 metre training track, several water tanks and 3 main dams.
Situated within 20 minutes of Geelong's CBD, 60 minutes to Melbourne and on the edge of the Drysdale township. Also it is in within easy reach of surf and recreational beaches, several golf courses and wineries, excellent primary and secondary schools and quality shopping facilities.
A wonderful lifestyle property awaits for you to create your dream home (STCA).
